## 5. Risks and Assumptions

### 5.1 Risks

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |
| OSV API rate limiting | Medium | Medium | Caching, batch queries |
| Secrets detection high false positives | High | High | Entropy threshold tuning, context analysis |
| Lockfile format changes | Medium | Low | Version-aware parsers |
| SARIF spec complexity | Low | Low | Use SARIF SDK/library |

### 5.2 Assumptions

* OSV API is freely available and reliable
* CycloneDX 1.5 is the current standard
* SARIF 2.1.0 is supported by major CI/CD platforms
* Shannon entropy > 4.5 is a good threshold for secrets
* Lockfiles contain sufficient data for SBOM generation

